        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The European production volume is extrapolated from the global production volume based on information from Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council) and the American Chemistry Council.
According to Cefic (2016), the global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3 534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per region are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (US, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%, Switzerland 1%. Cefic also reports the US total sales, which amount to 518.7 billion euros out of the global 3 534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported by the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to which the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016.
The production volume of RER is therefore estimated to be 17.4% of the global production volume.
The global production volume is estimated based on HERA (2009), according to which the global production volume is estimated to be 290000000 kg for the year 2003. Moreover, it is assumed that 50% of ethoxylated alcohols originate from vegetable oil sources whilst the remaining 50% comes from petrochemical origins. In addition, according to HERA (2009), the distribution of AE7 in household products is 7%.

Reference:
HERA 2009, Human &amp; Environmental Risk Assessment on ingredients of European household cleaning products, Alcohol Ethoxylates, September 2009. 
FAOSTAT, 2017, Food and Agricultural Organization of the United Nations. Accessible at: http://www.fao.org/faostat/en/#data/QD
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html""</productionVolumeComment>
